field.value:
It seems to me that JoinedBase doesn´t handle having CompositKey split between base class and derived class. 

More specifically I  have a structure like this:

class EventBase <- JoinBase (table has column "store_id" and has Property Store)
class MyEvent: EventBase <- JoinedKey (has column "scale_id" and property Scale which includes a Store)

MyEvent has method
[BelongsTo(
            CompositeKeyColumns = new string[] { "store_id", "scale_id" },
            Cascade = CascadeEnum.None,
            NotNull = true)]
        public Scale Scale
        {
            get { return _scale; }
            set { _scale = value; }
        }

where "store_id" is found in EventBase table and "scale_id" is found in MyEvent table

I get and error which informs me that "store_id" is an invalid column twice.

I´m guessing that the relation is not intelligent enaugh to check the JoinBase when resolving
